1
00:02:17,595 --> 00:02:20,180
Jackson, you really going to Hong Kong?

2
00:02:20,348 --> 00:02:23,517
I love anything with full contact.
Need a few more scars on my face.

3
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:25,644
I heard you can get killed at that kumite.

4
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:28,272
Only if you fuck up. Unh.

5
00:02:39,784 --> 00:02:42,077
Tomorrow we leave for the kumite.

6
00:03:02,265 --> 00:03:03,849
Sir?

7
00:03:04,684 --> 00:03:08,562
Excuse me, but Colonel Cooke would like
to see you before you leave on furlough.

8
00:03:08,938 --> 00:03:10,314
What's the problem?

9
00:03:10,648 --> 00:03:12,941
The colonel found out
you're going to Hong Kong.

10
00:03:13,109 --> 00:03:16,486
- He wants to talk to you about it.
- Tell him I'll be right there...

11
00:03:16,654 --> 00:03:17,821
...after I take a shower.

12
00:03:17,989 --> 00:03:19,489
But I'll have to wait, sir.

13
00:03:20,408 --> 00:03:21,825
Okay.

14
00:03:26,247 --> 00:03:28,457
What's taking so long, captain?

15
00:03:30,168 --> 00:03:31,710
Captain?

16
00:03:42,347 --> 00:03:43,972
Shit.

17
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:04,117
Sir.

18
00:04:04,285 --> 00:04:06,536
- Where's Dux?
- He was at the gym, like you said.

19
00:04:06,829 --> 00:04:08,997
He took a shower, I waited,
and he disappeared.

20
00:04:09,165 --> 00:04:12,668
- What do you mean, he disappeared?
- One minute he was there, next he wasn't.

21
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:15,045
If anything happens to Dux
in Hong Kong...

22
00:04:15,421 --> 00:04:17,547
Get Helmer and Rawlins on this
right away.

23
00:04:17,715 --> 00:04:21,510
And I don't wanna see your face again
until Dux is beside it. Understand?

24
00:04:41,364 --> 00:04:43,490
- How is he?
- He's resting now.

25
00:04:43,658 --> 00:04:45,450
He'll be so happy to see you.

26
00:04:45,702 --> 00:04:48,245
It's so good to be here again.

27
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:53,667
I'll tell him you are here.

28
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:55,419
Thank you.

29
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:16,982
Wow! Look at the sword.

30
00:05:23,656 --> 00:05:24,906
Let's get it.

31
00:05:25,074 --> 00:05:27,909
Come on, Frank.
What's the matter, you chicken?

32
00:05:28,077 --> 00:05:29,745
- No.
Then get in here.

33
00:05:29,912 --> 00:05:33,540
Hey, Frank, you wanna hang
out with us, then come on.

34
00:05:36,419 --> 00:05:38,754
You just gonna stand there
or are you gonna grab something?

35
00:05:40,131 --> 00:05:42,591
Shit. They're coming back.
Let's get out of here.

36
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:46,094
- Come on, Frank.
Forget him. Let's go.

37
00:06:04,822 --> 00:06:06,490
That's enough, Shingo.

38
00:06:06,657 --> 00:06:08,533
Go do your studies.

39
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:22,130
You cannot get katana sword by stealing.

40
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:25,467
It is a very special sword.

41
00:06:26,260 --> 00:06:28,011
You must earn it.

42
00:06:28,179 --> 00:06:29,971
I wasn't going to steal it.

43
00:06:35,728 --> 00:06:37,020
You didn't flinch.

44
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:39,106
You have fighting spirit.

45
00:06:39,482 --> 00:06:41,400
You're not gonna call the cops?

46
00:06:42,318 --> 00:06:44,027
Not if we make a deal.

47
00:06:44,237 --> 00:06:46,279
What kind of a deal?

48
00:06:46,697 --> 00:06:49,991
Your son and my son
are in the same school.

49
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:52,327
Frank sees my son's skill.

50
00:06:52,995 --> 00:06:56,581
And he desires
to learn martial science too.

51
00:06:56,749 --> 00:07:00,502
Yes, but what do you mean
by "martial science"?

52
00:07:01,379 --> 00:07:05,382
Frank tell me you came to America
to grow vine.

53
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:07,759
Yes, that's right.
I work at the Verne vineyard.

54
00:07:08,052 --> 00:07:11,513
I came here to grow fish in my hatchery.

55
00:07:12,181 --> 00:07:14,224
We both grow children.

56
00:07:14,392 --> 00:07:18,061
You use science
to make vines grow better.

57
00:07:18,229 --> 00:07:21,940
Like vines, children need training.

58
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:25,652
Martial science
provides a way of training.

59
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:29,906
Brings mind, body, spirit together.

60
00:07:35,329 --> 00:07:36,621
That's enough.

61
00:07:36,914 --> 00:07:39,166
- That's all for today.
- Not yet.

62
00:07:39,792 --> 00:07:41,293
Why don't you quit, round-eye?

63
00:07:43,045 --> 00:07:44,713
Not yet.

64
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,966
Go practice your katas.

65
00:07:49,635 --> 00:07:51,803
How come you coach him, but not me?

66
00:07:52,388 --> 00:07:55,515
I brought you here to help me train my son.
Don't question me.

67
00:07:55,850 --> 00:07:59,269
If you expect me to be his punching bag,
you can forget about our deal.

68
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:07,277
Yeah! Throw a punch.

69
00:08:23,085 --> 00:08:24,920
Someday...

70
00:08:25,087 --> 00:08:27,839
...I'll fight in the kumite
and make my father proud.

71
00:08:39,143 --> 00:08:43,647
Shidoshi, I feel like I've lost
a part of my family too.

72
00:08:43,814 --> 00:08:48,443
Shingo and I were close friends,
like brothers.

73
00:08:48,861 --> 00:08:51,446
And you and Mrs. Tanaka...

74
00:08:51,614 --> 00:08:55,575
...have treated me like a son.

75
00:09:00,414 --> 00:09:02,582
What will happen now?

76
00:09:03,626 --> 00:09:05,460
No more training.

77
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:07,212
I stop now.

78
00:09:12,134 --> 00:09:14,886
But you have so much to teach.

79
00:09:16,347 --> 00:09:17,639
You don't understand.

80
00:09:19,392 --> 00:09:22,644
In the war, I lost my first family:

81
00:09:23,312 --> 00:09:27,774
my son, daughter and wife.

82
00:09:30,444 --> 00:09:32,487
They lived in Hiroshima.

83
00:09:35,908 --> 00:09:39,035
I left Japan because of the war.

84
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:41,538
War was wrong.

85
00:09:42,623 --> 00:09:45,333
I came here to start over...

86
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:49,588
...begin a new family, have a son.

87
00:09:49,922 --> 00:09:52,757
Another chance to pass on the teaching.

88
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:55,677
For 2000 years...

89
00:09:56,887 --> 00:09:59,681
...knowledge passed from father to son...

90
00:09:59,849 --> 00:10:02,350
...father to son.

91
00:10:05,229 --> 00:10:07,188
When Shingo died...

92
00:10:08,190 --> 00:10:09,774
...it stopped.

93
00:10:13,237 --> 00:10:16,281
Teach me. I can do it.

94
00:10:16,699 --> 00:10:19,701
You are not Japanese.
You are not a Tanaka!

95
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:23,538
You taught me
using any technique that works...

96
00:10:23,706 --> 00:10:26,750
...never to limit myself to one style...

97
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:29,002
...to keep an open mind.

98
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:31,087
Why?

99
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:35,717
To honor you, shidoshi.

100
00:13:30,309 --> 00:13:32,727
Practice until you can meditate...

101
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:35,063
...and nothing can distract you...

102
00:13:35,231 --> 00:13:37,315
...so that you see and feel nothing...

103
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:39,859
...except your own energy.

104
00:16:54,013 --> 00:16:56,431
Are you awake, shidoshi?

105
00:16:57,599 --> 00:16:59,851
Do you sleep with your eyes open?

106
00:17:00,561 --> 00:17:01,811
How are you feeling?

107
00:17:04,565 --> 00:17:06,941
Like an old man.

108
00:17:08,152 --> 00:17:09,944
And how about you?

109
00:17:12,614 --> 00:17:14,699
I'm going to Hong Kong.

110
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:16,242
You sure you want to do this?

111
00:17:17,494 --> 00:17:22,623
To honor you means everything to me.

112
00:17:23,792 --> 00:17:26,544
I have poured all my knowledge into you.

113
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:31,716
When you fight,
my spirit will fight with you.

114
00:17:33,135 --> 00:17:36,137
In kumite, you will need it.

115
00:18:15,302 --> 00:18:18,221
Hey, babe,
wanna go out with a real big man?

116
00:18:18,388 --> 00:18:20,056
No, huh?

117
00:18:26,772 --> 00:18:29,315
Too handsome for you, huh, honey?

118
00:18:34,446 --> 00:18:36,697
This your first time in Hong Kong?

119
00:18:37,407 --> 00:18:39,867
You two are here for the kumite,
aren't you?

120
00:18:40,035 --> 00:18:43,204
Kumite? What is kumite?

121
00:18:43,872 --> 00:18:46,958
Look, guys,
I know there's a secret full-contact event...

122
00:18:47,126 --> 00:18:49,335
...being held in Hong Kong
in the next few days.

123
00:18:49,753 --> 00:18:52,338
Yes. Hong Kong is an exciting city.

124
00:18:52,881 --> 00:18:55,967
I also happen to know a little bit
about some of your competition.

125
00:18:58,095 --> 00:18:59,679
Okay. Um...

126
00:19:00,806 --> 00:19:02,765
Would you just tell me
how you got invited?

127
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:09,897
Thanks, guys.

128
00:19:18,198 --> 00:19:21,409
What?
Think you can give me some competition?

129
00:19:21,577 --> 00:19:23,578
Sure. I'll try.

130
00:19:23,954 --> 00:19:27,540
That's what I like to hear,
a kid who isn't afraid to lose.

131
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:30,710
No, no, I got it.
I don't want to take your money.

132
00:19:32,379 --> 00:19:34,714
- You ready?
- Yeah.

133
00:20:02,159 --> 00:20:04,785
- You like this kind of fighting, huh?
- Yeah.

134
00:20:05,287 --> 00:20:08,956
If you want to see some real fighting,
you can see me fight at the kumite.

135
00:20:09,124 --> 00:20:11,417
I'm here, too, for the kumite.

136
00:20:11,919 --> 00:20:14,503
Aren't you a little young for full contact?

137
00:20:14,671 --> 00:20:18,341
Aren't you a little old for video games?

138
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:21,469
- You want to go at it again, huh?
- Yeah.

139
00:20:35,525 --> 00:20:37,652
Not bad, kid. Name's Ray Jackson.

140
00:20:37,819 --> 00:20:38,861
I'm Frank Dux.

141
00:20:47,663 --> 00:20:48,871
Ms. Tanaka...

142
00:20:49,039 --> 00:20:51,415
- Mrs. Tanaka?
- Y es?

143
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:55,002
Mrs. Tanaka, it's very important
to the government of the United States...

144
00:20:55,170 --> 00:20:56,796
...that we find Frank Dux.

145
00:20:56,964 --> 00:21:00,508
We understand that he might have visited
Mr. Tanaka here recently.

146
00:21:00,801 --> 00:21:03,135
Mr. Tanaka is very ill.

147
00:21:03,303 --> 00:21:05,513
We're sorry to hear that.

148
00:21:06,139 --> 00:21:07,640
Was Frank here recently?

149
00:21:08,058 --> 00:21:10,643
Frank came here to pay his respects.

150
00:21:10,811 --> 00:21:12,812
- When was that?
- Two days ago.

151
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:16,440
Did he say or do you know
if he was going to Hong Kong?

152
00:21:17,526 --> 00:21:18,567
I don't know.

153
00:21:18,735 --> 00:21:20,861
Of course you know.
Look, we're not trying to-

154
00:21:21,029 --> 00:21:24,907
Mrs. Tanaka,
we're very sorry to have disturbed you.

155
00:21:25,075 --> 00:21:27,410
Thank you very much for your time.

156
00:21:33,959 --> 00:21:35,751
May I help you?
How you doing?

157
00:21:35,919 --> 00:21:38,879
My name's Jackson. This is Mr. Frank Dux.
Are our rooms ready?

158
00:21:39,047 --> 00:21:42,842
Mr. Lin in Room 310
wants to see you after you check in.

159
00:21:43,343 --> 00:21:44,927
Who the hell's Mr. Lin?

160
00:21:45,095 --> 00:21:48,306
I'm Lin. You Jackson?
You look like a Jackson.

161
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:53,102
That would make you Frank Dux.

162
00:21:53,270 --> 00:21:55,771
No, no, no. It's Dux.

163
00:21:55,939 --> 00:21:58,107
Gotcha. Like "Put up your dukes," right?

164
00:21:58,859 --> 00:22:00,526
Okay, so here's the deal.

165
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:02,570
This is the biggest kumite ever.

166
00:22:02,738 --> 00:22:04,405
We got fighters from all over.

167
00:22:05,073 --> 00:22:06,824
I've been assigned by the IFAA...

168
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:09,535
...to help you
and the other North American fighters...

169
00:22:09,703 --> 00:22:11,579
...to find your way around.

170
00:22:11,747 --> 00:22:14,081
I'm gonna make sure
you guys give it your best...

171
00:22:14,249 --> 00:22:16,751
...and don't disqualify by fighting
outside the arena.

172
00:22:18,253 --> 00:22:21,130
The Triad-
They are like the mafia.

173
00:22:21,298 --> 00:22:24,592
- is allowing us
to hold kumite here this time.

174
00:22:28,305 --> 00:22:31,057
Here it comes, man, the Walled City.

175
00:22:31,224 --> 00:22:33,184
Not a place for outsiders.

176
00:22:33,352 --> 00:22:34,894
You are in Hong Kong.

177
00:22:35,062 --> 00:22:38,856
But you are about to cross
an invisible border into mainland China.

178
00:22:39,358 --> 00:22:42,693
No joke, man.
It's a run-down piece of no man's land...

179
00:22:42,861 --> 00:22:44,945
...in the middle of a tourist paradise.

180
00:22:45,113 --> 00:22:49,075
Goes way back to the old lease agreement
between Great Britain and China.

181
00:22:49,242 --> 00:22:52,495
Once you step out of the sunlight
into the narrow corridors...

182
00:22:52,662 --> 00:22:55,456
...it's time to protect your nuts, guys.

183
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:08,135
Okay, U.S.A.

184
00:23:09,971 --> 00:23:11,972
"Okay, U.S.A."

185
00:25:20,435 --> 00:25:21,852
Okay, guys.

186
00:25:22,020 --> 00:25:25,814
First, you can show the Black Dragon boys
your invitation.

187
00:25:25,982 --> 00:25:28,859
Then you got to qualify
and prove to them...

188
00:25:29,027 --> 00:25:32,154
...you can step onto the runway
and not get killed.

189
00:25:32,322 --> 00:25:33,781
- Got it?
- Mm-hm.

190
00:25:34,616 --> 00:25:36,075
You got it?

191
00:25:36,576 --> 00:25:37,826
Mm-hm.

192
00:25:54,928 --> 00:25:58,639
It says he represents the Tanaka clan.

193
00:25:59,808 --> 00:26:01,433
You don't look like Tanaka.

194
00:26:01,851 --> 00:26:03,686
Shidoshi Tanaka trained me.

195
00:26:04,145 --> 00:26:05,145
What's the holdup?

196
00:26:05,313 --> 00:26:08,774
He says Senzo Tanaka is his shidoshi.

197
00:26:08,942 --> 00:26:11,986
What's the difference
if Bruce Springsteen is his shidoshi?

198
00:26:12,153 --> 00:26:14,989
If Senzo Tanaka is his shidoshi...

199
00:26:15,156 --> 00:26:17,283
...then show us the din mak.

200
00:26:17,450 --> 00:26:19,868
What the hell is a din mak?

201
00:26:20,537 --> 00:26:21,787
Death touch.

202
00:26:30,380 --> 00:26:31,839
Thanks.

203
00:26:33,008 --> 00:26:35,551
Vic, choose a brick.

204
00:26:36,177 --> 00:26:37,845
Okay, Frank.

205
00:26:38,513 --> 00:26:41,390
Uh, what about this one?

206
00:26:48,690 --> 00:26:50,065
No!

207
00:26:52,652 --> 00:26:54,445
Bottom one.

208
00:27:26,686 --> 00:27:28,520
Whoa! Yeah!

209
00:27:34,402 --> 00:27:36,028
Son of the bitch.

210
00:27:36,196 --> 00:27:37,780
Is that good enough, guys?

211
00:27:39,115 --> 00:27:41,116
We honor your invitation.

212
00:27:41,576 --> 00:27:43,285
No shit, you honor his invitation.

213
00:27:45,705 --> 00:27:47,039
That was great.

214
00:27:54,422 --> 00:27:56,298
Very good...

215
00:27:56,466 --> 00:27:58,967
...but brick not hit back.

216
00:28:17,320 --> 00:28:20,155
Here's a picture of the man
that we're looking for.

217
00:28:20,323 --> 00:28:23,283
His name is Frank Dux.

218
00:28:23,952 --> 00:28:27,287
We have reason to believe
Frank is here in Hong Kong.

219
00:28:27,455 --> 00:28:29,123
His name was on a list...

220
00:28:29,290 --> 00:28:31,458
...on a flight from San Francisco
two days ago.

221
00:28:31,626 --> 00:28:32,918
Two days ago?

222
00:28:33,086 --> 00:28:35,212
Maybe he already left,
went somewhere else.

223
00:28:35,380 --> 00:28:37,673
Ha. Asia's a very big place, you know.

224
00:28:37,841 --> 00:28:40,467
We were hoping you would hold onto this
for reference.

225
00:28:40,635 --> 00:28:43,345
We're here because Frank
is going to fight in the kumite...

226
00:28:43,513 --> 00:28:45,431
...and we're here to stop him.

227
00:28:48,351 --> 00:28:49,977
The kumite?

228
00:28:50,854 --> 00:28:52,271
Yes.

229
00:29:06,661 --> 00:29:08,370
Inspector Chen.

230
00:29:08,538 --> 00:29:11,999
We all know that the kumite
is happening here in Hong Kong.

231
00:29:12,167 --> 00:29:15,419
And we all know it's going on
over the next three days.

232
00:29:16,838 --> 00:29:19,840
Look, all we want you to do
is pass this picture out to your men.

233
00:29:20,008 --> 00:29:22,676
They spot Dux,
they give us a call at our hotel. Simple.

234
00:29:23,011 --> 00:29:25,179
My men already overworked.

235
00:29:25,805 --> 00:29:28,974
- Hey, if it's too much trouble, forget it-
Inspector.

236
00:29:29,142 --> 00:29:33,020
We're all overworked,
but we need your help.

237
00:29:34,105 --> 00:29:35,856
I'll see what can be done.

238
00:29:36,608 --> 00:29:38,317
You know where to reach us?

239
00:29:39,736 --> 00:29:41,320
Mm-hm.

240
00:29:41,488 --> 00:29:43,989
You come upstairs with me
for an interview.

241
00:29:44,157 --> 00:29:45,449
Like hell. Let go of me.

242
00:29:45,617 --> 00:29:47,284
You want Hossein, no?

243
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:48,869
No. Hossein is an asshole.

244
00:29:49,037 --> 00:29:50,746
What did you call me?

245
00:29:50,914 --> 00:29:53,207
You want me to spell it out for you?

246
00:29:58,755 --> 00:30:00,088
Leave the girl alone.

247
00:30:00,256 --> 00:30:03,342
He is the American shithead
who makes tricks with bricks.

248
00:30:03,510 --> 00:30:05,844
Guess the kumite starts
one day earlier this year.

249
00:30:06,012 --> 00:30:08,639
- Look, guys, let's all just calm down, okay?
- No.

250
00:30:08,807 --> 00:30:10,599
She is coming with me upstairs.

251
00:30:10,767 --> 00:30:11,850
No, I'm not.

252
00:30:12,018 --> 00:30:13,435
If we have to fight for her...

253
00:30:13,603 --> 00:30:17,397
...then both of us would be thrown
out of the kumite.

254
00:30:18,066 --> 00:30:19,775
Just for her?

255
00:30:20,985 --> 00:30:23,403
We could arrange this another way.

